          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Innate immunity is the first line of defense against infection. it is non specific. It is the resistance to infections that an individual possess by viue of his or her genetic and constitutional make up. Reference : Anathanarayan & paniker's 9th edition, pg no:78 <\\p>",
