          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Ans. (d) Onchocerca volvulusRef: Diagnostic medical parasitology 3rd/275, Park 19th /221* Onchocerca volvulus results in river blindness and subcutaneous nodules.* \"Lymphatic filariasis\" covers infection with three closely related nematode worms - W.Bancrofti, B. Malayi and B. timoria.* All three infections are transmitted to man by the bites of infective mosquitoes.* All three parasites have basically similar life cycles in man- adult worms living in lymphatic vessels whilst their offspring, the microfilariae circulate in peripheral bloodand are available to infect mosquito vectors when they come to feed.Also Know* Diethylcarbamazine (DEC) is the drug of choice for filariasis.* Ivermectin is the drug of choice for Onchocerca volvulus",
          "hint": "Topic: Mycology"
