          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Ans. is 'c' i.e., Mycetoma o Mycetoma are chronic, slowly progressive infections of the subcutaneous tissue usually of the foot caused by a number of Actinomycetes and filamentous fungi.o The disease usually begins as a small subcutaneous swelling of the foot, which enlarges, burrowing into deeper tissues and tracking to the surface as multiple sinuses discharging viscid, seropurulent fluid containing granules.",
          "hint": "Topic: Actinomycetes"
