          "id": "medmcqa-27fdb198-e17c-40d0-a02e-8a5e985f6066",
          "text": "A 16-year-old girl presents with a painfully enlarged lymph node in her right axilla and low grade fever. Peripheral blood counts are within normal limits. The lymph node is biopsied, and numerous granulomas filled with neutrophils and necrotic debris are observed. Which of the following organisms could produce this disease?",
