          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "The T helper cells (Th cells) are a type of T cell that play an impoant role in the immune system, paicularly in the adaptive immune system. They help the activity of other immune cells by releasing T cell cytokines. These cells help suppress or regulate immune responses. They are essential in B cell antibody class switching, in the activation and growth of cytotoxic T cells, and in maximizing bactericidal activity of phagocytes such as macrophages. Reff: Ananthanarayanan & panikers textbook of microbiology 9th edition pg:135",
