          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Anti-centromere antibodies are a marker for the CREST (calcinosis, Raynaud's phenomenon, esophageal dysfunction, sclerodactyly, and telangiectasia) variant of scleroderma. The markers for diffuse scleroderma, anti-Scl-70 and anti-Pol-I, are usually negative in CREST syndrome, as are most other autoantibodies. The marker for mixed connective tissue disease is anti-RNP. The markers for Sjogren's syndrome are anti-SSA, anti-SSB, and anti-RAP"
