          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Giardia can cause traveller's diarrhea.\nOther protozoal causes of traveller's diarrhea\n\n\nEntamoeba histolytica\nCyclospora\nCryptosporidium\n\n\nGiardia inhabits the proximal small intestine i..e, duodenum and upper jejunum (not ileum)\n\n\nThe infective stage for giardia infection is a cyst (not trophozoites)."
