          "explanation": "The symptoms of the given case are suggestive of C. diphtheria infection.\n\nOn Loeffler’s serum slope, C. diphtheriae grows after 4–6 hours at 37°C producing small, circular, and white opaque colonies. \nIf no colonies are seen, the medium is reincubated further for 24 hours.\n\nParija SC. Textbook of Microbiology & Immunology. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2014. Page:218"
