          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "The adult worm lives in the human intestine, usually in the jejunum, where it lies in several folds in the lumen. Commonly only a single worm is present, but rarely several worms may be seen, upto 25 or more in a patient Ref: panickers textbook of Medical parasitology 8th edition ...page :115",
          "hint": "Topic: parasitology"
