          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Several viruses can lead to viral pneumonia, including:\n\nAdenoviruses, which can also cause the common cold and bronchitis.\nChickenpox (Varicella-zoster virus).\nFlu (influenza viruses).\nRespiratory syncytial virus, which causes cold-like symptoms.\nCytomegalovirus, measles, retrovirus.\n\nMumps is an acute infectious disease of children, characterized by acute, nonsuppurative, painful swelling of the salivary glands, caused by mumps virus.\n \nParija SC. Textbook of Microbiology & Immunology. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2014. Page:519"
