          "id": "medmcqa-2a11edd1-d024-4265-be61-fd39b232b6ed",
          "text": "A 24-year-old sex worker from Mumbai develops chronic abdominal pain, low-grade fever, diarrhea, and malabsorption. He saw later found to be positive for HIV. Oocysts are demonstrated in the stool. Which of the following organisms is most likely to be the cause of the patient's diarrhea?",
