          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Ans. is 'd' i.e., Flagillary hemagglutinin, peussis toxin, fimbrial . Acellular peussis vaccines currently available from different manufactures should be considered as different and unique products because of the presence of one or more different components which are: - Chemically or genetically detoxified peussis toxin (PT toxoid). - Filamentous hemagglutinin - 69k Da outer membrane protein ( also known as peactin). - Fimbrial-2 and fimbrial-3 antigens."
