          "id": "medmcqa-b6fc1162-154f-4b07-b09c-8ddd0ce5b1f2",
          "text": "A sexually active young male, presented to the physician with urethral discharge. On urine microbiology examination, pus cells were present in the absence of any identifiable organisms. Which of the following is the best method for culture in this this scenario?",
